column.name: UMREGION
column.comment: Region code depending on the database in CableMaster,where the data is extracted from.

column.name: SETYPE
column.comment: Billing Type. This code helps determine the rate that will be available to the customer.  It indicates whether the account is: C=Commercial, S=Single Family, M=Multi Family

column.name: SESRCD
column.comment: The code specifying a service a customer has ordered, an install or deposit fee a customer has been charged, or a special request a customer has asked to be performed

column.name: SESPRT
column.comment:
identifies the primary rate, including any taxes, for the service.

Depending on the definition in SESTYP, SEROVR, SEMFLG, or SEMNVL. The CSR may overwrite the pricing. The final price for the customer can be found in SRVR/WORDD

column.name: SESART
column.comment:
identifies any additional charges, including any taxes, for the service, e.g. service fee, recurring, may be empty

Depending on the definition in SESTYP, SEROVR, SEMFLG,or SEMNVL. The CSR may overwrite the pricing. The final price for the customer can be found in SRVR/WORDD

column.name: SESCYY
column.comment: Identifies the date the rate will start to be in effect CYY (C=Century; YY=Year)

column.name: SESMM
column.comment: Identifies the date the rate will start to be in effect MM (MM=Month)

column.name: SESDD
column.comment: Identifies the date the rate will start to be in effect DD (DD=Day

column.name: SEECYY
column.comment: Identifies the date the rate will expire CYY (C=Century; YY=Year)

column.name: SEEMM
column.comment: Identifies the date the rate will expire MM (MM=Month)

column.name: SEEDD
column.comment: Identifies the date the rate will expire DD (DD=Day)

column.name: SESTYP
column.comment: It specifies the type of service the related service code represents.

column.name: SEPROT
column.comment: Prorate Indicator: Y = a service that is added to a work order qualifies to receive a prorated portion of the rate; N = a service added does not qualify for a prorated portion of the rate

column.name: SEADRR
column.comment: Addressable Indicator Y/N: Identifies with the service needs to be signaled on the converter or piece of equipment

column.name: SEBALC
column.comment: Balance override Y/N: Enter a 'Y' in this field so that this service is not required to be fully balanced on the Customer balancing screen.

column.name: SECATG
column.comment:
Category A-H: 
Category refers to the column in the Matrix Table in which the service is located.

Matrix tables are currently not in use at UM.

column.name: SEWGHT
column.comment:
Weight 1-9: 
The weight refers to the priority that a particular service has within the category to which it belongs. One of the functions of the matrix tables is to allow discounting to take place if a customer subscribes to more than one service which belongs to a particular category.

Matrix tables are currently not in use at UM.

column.name: SEPEG
column.comment:
Peg Y/N: Enter a 'Y' in the Peg service field if you want services to be pegged for matrix pricing. A peg value will then have to be entered (1-9) in the subsequent field. This value determines which discounted rate the service will receive within the matrix tables. If you do not want pegging to be effective, enter an 'N' in the Peg service field, and leave the Peg value field blank.
Matrix tables are currently not in use at UM.

column.name: SEROVR
column.comment:
Allow rate override: All deposit, installation, and SRO services are displayed in the One-time charges section within order entry. The Amount column on the OTC section shows the service rate that has been entered within the rate master file. Enter a 'Y' in this field if you would like the CSR to be able to change the rate for this service from order entry. If not, enter an 'N' and the Amount field for this service will be protected on the One-time charges screen.
The final rate can be found in the Work Order Detail WORDD table.

column.name: SEPERD
column.comment: Default charge period: Identifies the billing frequency codes (e.g. A = Annual, M = Monthly, etc).

column.name: SEPOVR
column.comment: Allow period override Y/blank: A 'Y' in this field will allow the user to override the service-level default charge period set up in the 'Default charge period' field. If the Allow charge period override field is not set to 'Y', the charge period used will be the one from the customer's account record, regardless of the setting of the Default charge period code on the rate master file.

column.name: SEMFLG
column.comment: Manual price entry flag: The entry made in this field governs whether or not the primary and auxiliary price fields on the Billing services screen can be manually changed by the CSR during order entry. Valid entries in the Manual rate entry flag are: 1 = Prohibit manual price entry (this is the default); 2 = Force manual price entry; or 3 = Optional manual price entry; 4 = allow different prices than the primary rate but should not allow manual override

column.name: SEMINP
column.comment: Min. contract period months, maybe overwritten, too. Final contract duration in customer-related data.

column.name: SEOESQ
column.comment: Order entry sequence code: Enter a sequence number in this field. This controls the sequencing of services in order entry, with a customer's existing, active services always appearing at the top of the service list. This sequence code is five digits in length to allow a sensible interval between each service for subsequent easy insertion of new services. If no value is entered here, services will be displayed in the category and weight sequence.

column.name: SEINCQ
column.comment: Use qty in service count for matrix range? Y/N

column.name: SEDBIL
column.comment: Daily billing Y/N: Identifies whether service is eligible for daily billing. Not used by UM and is defaulted as "N"

column.name: SEDTYP
column.comment: Deposit type: E - Indicates that the adjustment should affect the equipment deposit, S - indicates that the adjustment should affect the service deposit, Blank - if it should not affect equipment/service deposit records. Not Used by UM

column.name: SESVGP
column.comment:
Service group: Service Group is used to group similar service codes together on an account during Order
Entry.

column.name: SESRTY
column.comment: Service type: It categorizes the type of service the related service code represents. These types are defined as follows: B = Basic Service, P = Premium Service. Primary used for reporting and matrix analysis.

column.name: SEMCLS
column.comment: Major class code R/B/blank: ‘B’ if this service is only allowed for business customers or ‘R’ if it is only allowed for residential customers. Blank if the service is available to both types of customers.

column.name: SELUSR
column.comment: Last user to update this record

column.name: SEDD2
column.comment: Payment method D/N/blank: If this service is only available to direct debit payers, filled with ‘D’. If this service is only available to non-direct debit payers, filled with ‘N’. Blank if this service is available to both direct debit and non-direct debit payers

column.name: SEUT2
column.comment:
User Type: Describes the Type of User allowed to sell service. AG=AGENT
CC=CALL CENTRE USER
FS=FIELD SALES AGENT
IT=IT TEST
RA= RETENTION AGENCY
RT=RETAILER
WS=WEB SELF CARE

column.name: SEDD3
column.comment: Payment method D/N/blank:  If this service is only available to direct debit payers, filled with ‘D’. If this service is only available to non-direct debit payers, filled with ‘N’. Blank if this service is available to both direct debit and non-direct debit payers

column.name: SEUT3
column.comment:
User Type: Describes the Type of User allowed to sell service. AG=AGENT
CC=CALL CENTRE USER
FS=FIELD SALES AGENT
IT=IT TEST
RA= RETENTION AGENCY
RT=RETAILER
WS=WEB SELF CARE

column.name: SEDD4
column.comment: Payment method D/N/blank:  If this service is only available to direct debit payers, filled with ‘D’. If this service is only available to non-direct debit payers, filled with ‘N’. Blank if this service is available to both direct debit and non-direct debit payers

column.name: SEUT4
column.comment:
User Type: Describes the Type of User allowed to sell service. AG=AGENT
CC=CALL CENTRE USER
FS=FIELD SALES AGENT
IT=IT TEST
RA= RETENTION AGENCY
RT=RETAILER
WS=WEB SELF CARE

column.name: SEMNVL
column.comment: Minimum rate value: controls whether the CSR during order entry can override the price to a value less than the amount entered in this field
